","city:2585","region:2009424","poi:36125237","country:75","continent:4"],"perex":"Also called the \'New Tokyo Tower\', this majestic monument is a must-see for any visitor of Tokyo.","customer_rating":null,"star_rating":null,"star_rating_unofficial":null,"thumbnail_url":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/poi:19839","tags":[{"key":"Observation Tower","name":"Observation Tower"},{"key":"Scenic Lookout","name":"Scenic Lookout"},{"key":"Neo-Futurist Architecture","name":"Neo-Futurist Architecture"},{"key":"Tower","name":"Tower"},{"key":"Skyscraper","name":"Skyscraper"},{"key":"View Point","name":"View Point"},{"key":"Modern Architecture","name":"Modern Architecture"}],"area":2505,"address":"13, 131-0045, 墨田区, JP","admission":"Tembo deck (350 m) \nDay ticket: \nAdults: 2.060 JPY \nChildren (12-17): 1.540 JPY \nChildren (6-11): 930 JPY \nChildren (4-5): 620 JPY \n\nTembo galleria (450 m) \nTickets purchased on the day only: \nAdults: 1.030 JPY \nChildren (12-17): 820 JPY \nChildren (6-11): 510 JPY \nChildren (4-5): 310 JPY \n\nCombo tickets:\nAdults (12+): 4.000 JPY\nChildren (4-11): 2.000 JPY\n\nWalk-in tickets can be purchased with no assigned time slot at the 4th floor. Tickets for a specified time slot can be reserved through the website in advance only with a Japanese credit card.","email":null,"opening_hours":null,"is_deleted":false,"phone":"+81 570 55 0634","description":{"text":"Also called the \'New Tokyo Tower\', this majestic monument is a must-see for any visitor of Tokyo. It offers an amazing view of as far as 70 kilometres in the distance.\n\nWith a height of 634 meters, the Skytree was the tallest building in Japan and the tallest tower in the world at the time of its completion in 2011. It even held the Guinness World record. \n\nThe height of the tower is interesting since the numbers 6, 3 and 4 can be read as syllables Mu, Sa and Shi in Japanese. Musashi is the name of the district of Tokyo in which the tower is located.\n\nThe Skytree has two separate observation decks. The lower, called Tembo Deck, hangs at the height of 350 meters. You can enjoy a cup of coffee here while looking at the city around in a 360 degrees view. The upper, called Tembo Galleria, is placed at the height of 450 meters. You can only access it if you purchase a separate ticket at the tower.","provider":null,"translation_provider":null,"link":null,"is_translated":true},"opening_hours_raw":"Mo-Su 08:00-21:00","media_count":10,"main_media":{"usage":{"square":"m:2853242","video_preview":null,"portrait":"m:2853245","landscape":"m:2615254"},"media":[{"original":{"size":null,"width":3072,"height":2056},"suitability":["square"],"url_template":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/{size}/612664395a40232133447d33247d3832383533323432","created_at":"1970-01-01T00:00:00+0000","source":{"provider":"wikipedia","name":"Wikimedia Commons","external_id":null},"type":"photo","created_by":"53d8a9428f8ff","url":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/612664395a40232133447d33247d3832383533323432.jpg","quadkey":null,"attribution":{"title_url":"http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Tokyo_Sky_tree.jpg","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0","other":null,"author_url":"http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Br1xxxx","author":"Br1xxxx","title":"The Tokyo Sky tree is still under construction when picture was taken, stands 634m. It is the worlds tallest broadcast tower in the world.","license_url":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0"},"location":null,"id":"m:2853242"},{"original":{"size":null,"width":2500,"height":1688},"suitability":["landscape"],"url_template":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/{size}/612664395a40232133447d33247d3832363135323534","created_at":"2015-03-18T10:47:11+0000","source":{"provider":"wikipedia","name":"Wikimedia Commons","external_id":null},"type":"photo","created_by":"52ebb4fe049c5","url":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/612664395a40232133447d33247d3832363135323534.jpg","quadkey":null,"attribution":{"