"city:2585","region:465","region:2009424","poi:28260670","country:75","continent:4"],"perex":"The Tokyo National Museum, or TNM, established in 1872, is the oldest Japanese national museum, the largest art museum in Japan and one of…","customer_rating":null,"star_rating":null,"star_rating_unofficial":null,"thumbnail_url":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/poi:19827","tags":[{"key":"Japanese Art","name":"Japanese Art"},{"key":"Art Collections","name":"Art Collections"},{"key":"Asian Art","name":"Asian Art"},{"key":"National Museum","name":"National Museum"},{"key":"Museum","name":"Museum"},{"key":"Art","name":"Art"},{"key":"Art Museum","name":"Art Museum"},{"key":"Art Gallery","name":"Art Gallery"}],"area":103622,"address":"13-9 Uenokoen, Taito, Tokyo 110-8712, Japan","admission":"Adults: 620 JPY\nUniversity Students: JPY 410\nStudents, children, seniors (70+): free\n\nAdmission to regular exhibitions is free on: International Museum Day, and Respect for the Aged Day (3rd Mon of Sep).","email":null,"opening_hours":"(Last admission 30 min before closing.)\n\nClosed during year-end holidays. The opening hours may change due to holidays or special exhibitions, please, check the official website for detailed information.","is_deleted":false,"phone":"+81 3 5777 8600","description":{"text":"The Tokyo National Museum, or TNM, established in 1872, is the oldest Japanese national museum, the largest art museum in Japan and one of the largest art museums in the world. The museum collects, houses, and preserves a comprehensive collection of art works and archaeological objects of Asia, focusing on Japan. The museum holds over 110,000 objects, which includes 87 Japanese National Treasure holdings and 610 Important Cultural Property holdings. The museum also conducts research and organizes educational events related to its collection.\n\nThe museum is located inside Ueno Park in Taitō, Tokyo. The facilities consist of the Honkan, Tōyōkan, Hyōkeikan, Heiseikan, Hōryū-ji Hōmotsukan, as well as Shiryōkan, and other facilities. There are restaurants and shops within the museum\'s premises, as well as outdoor exhibitions and a garden where visitors can enjoy seasonal views.","provider":"wikipedia","translation_provider":null,"link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tokyo_National_Museum","is_translated":true},"opening_hours_raw":"09:30-17:00","media_count":6,"main_media":{"usage":{"square":"m:2854407","video_preview":null,"portrait":"m:2854407","landscape":"m:2854407"},"media":[{"original":{"size":null,"width":2684,"height":1720},"suitability":["square","landscape","portrait"],"url_template":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/{size}/612664395a40232133447d33247d3832383534343037","created_at":"2015-04-27T17:48:49+0000","source":{"provider":"wikipedia","name":"Wikimedia Commons","external_id":null},"type":"photo","created_by":"53d8a9428f8ff","url":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/612664395a40232133447d33247d3832383534343037.jpg","quadkey":"100110010110011010","attribution":{"title_url":"http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Heiseikan_of_Tokyo_National_Museum.jpg","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0","other":null,"author_url":"http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Wiiii","author":"Wiiii","title":"Heiseikan of Tokyo National Museum, at Taito-ku Tokyo Japan.","license_url":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0"},"location":{"lat":139.775556,"lng":35.72},"id":"m:2854407"}]},"references":[{"id":1480414,"title":"Wikipedia","type":"wiki","language_id":"en","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tokyo_National_Museum","supplier":"wiki","priority":0,"currency":null,"price":null,"flags":[]},{"id":1341251,"title":"Official Website","type":"link:official","language_id":null,"url":"http://www.tnm.jp/","supplier":null,"priority":0,"currency":null,"price":null,"flags":[]},{"id":14553492,"title":"About Tokyo/Ueno","type":"guide","language_id":"en","url":"https://guides.travel.sygic.com/production/en/Tokyo/Ueno","supplier":"wikivoyage","pr