freshment such as matcha and Japanese sweets in a tea-ceremony style. The garden has a peony garden, a plum tree grove and cosmos fields with flowers for every season. Japanese falconry and aikido are demonstrated at New Year.","provider":"wikipedia","translation_provider":null,"link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamarikyu_Gardens","is_translated":true},"opening_hours_raw":"09:00-17:00; Dec 29-Jan 1: off","media_count":13,"main_media":{"usage":{"square":"m:32597822","video_preview":null,"portrait":"m:32597814","landscape":"m:2853937"},"media":[{"original":{"size":null,"width":3072,"height":2304},"suitability":["square"],"url_template":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/{size}/612664395a40232133447d33247d383332353937383232","created_at":"2016-11-13T09:37:14+0000","source":{"provider":"wikipedia","name":"Wikimedia Commons","external_id":null},"type":"photo","created_by":"56d5ac07b3881","url":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/612664395a40232133447d33247d383332353937383232.jpg","quadkey":"100110010101101111","attribution":{"title_url":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Inabu_Shrine_110925_1.jpg","license":"CC0","other":null,"author_url":"http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Ulkl","author":"Ulf Klingström","title":"Former Inabu Shrine at Hama-Rikyu garden, Tokyo, Japan.","license_url":"http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/deed.en"},"location":{"lat":139.765639,"lng":35.661056},"id":"m:32597822"},{"original":{"size":null,"width":3072,"height":2304},"suitability":["landscape"],"url_template":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/{size}/612664395a40232133447d33247d3832383533393337","created_at":"2015-04-27T15:31:10+0000","source":{"provider":"wikipedia","name":"Wikimedia Commons","external_id":null},"type":"photo","created_by":"53d8a9428f8ff","url":"https://media-cdn.sygictraveldata.com/media/612664395a40232133447d33247d3832383533393337.jpg","quadkey":"100110010101101111","attribution":{"title_url":"http://commons.wikimedia.